Mechanism.

In January 2008 the original series was released on DVD in the UK by Network and Granada. It features all of the 13 original episodes unedited and remastered.
Barrage began as a musical entertainment concept created in Calgary, Alberta in 1996 by musicians Dean Marshall and John Crozman. Together with Jana Wyber, Brian Hanson, and Anthony Moore, they formed Barrage's executive production and creative team, known as "5 to 1 Entertainments".
July 2008 saw Carmel stage their biggest project yet with the establishing of an eight-team European Twenty20 Championship tournament which featured Estonia and Russia following the club's trip to the two countries the previous summer. Also involved were the national teams of Slovakia, Croatia, Czech Republic and a Poland as well as a Cricket Board of Wales representative side.
